# ETL Assignment

## Question 1: Define Data Transformation in ETL and explain why it is important.

Data Transformation in ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) is the process of converting raw data into a structured and usable format before loading it into a target system such as a data warehouse.

It is important because:
- It improves data quality.
- It ensures consistency in data.
- It removes errors and duplicates.
- It prepares data for analysis and reporting.

