## Question 6: What is One-Hot Encoding? Give an example with the categories: "Red, Blue, Green".

One-Hot Encoding is a method to convert categorical data into numerical format by creating separate binary columns for each category.

Example:

| Color | Red | Blue | Green |
|-------|-----|------|-------|
| Red   | 1   | 0    | 0     |
| Blue  | 0   | 1    | 0     |
| Green | 0   | 0    | 1     |

