## Question 8: Explain why Z-score Standardization is preferred over Min-Max Scaling when outliers exist.

Z-score Standardization uses mean and standard deviation, so it is less affected by extreme values.

Min-Max Scaling depends on minimum and maximum values, so outliers can heavily distort the results.

Therefore, Z-score Standardization is preferred when outliers are present.
